  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "Site Engineer",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Descriptions:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>To manage and support the field operations on projects.</li>\n  <li>Report to the Project Manager but primary responsibility will be to ensure the site supervisor and workers have the materials, equipment, and information necessary to complete the job.</li>\n  <li>As an extension of the Project Manager, you are ultimately responsible for understanding and accomplishing the customer’s goals while protecting and promoting the interests of company in all matters.</li>\n  <li>Determining client’s requirements and translating them into an actionable plan by a team of workers</li>\n  <li>Organizing many tasks into a timeline.</li>\n  <li>Assuring that all deadlines are being met.</li>\n  <li>Develop project specific Safety Programs in coordination with Safety Manager and Project Manager. Making sure that all health, safety and legal requirements are being met throughout the process</li>\n  <li>Responding to any client complaints, concerns or requests throughout the project</li>\n  <li>Holding regular meetings to ensure that everything is going according to time and budget restrictions</li>\n  <li>Support field in expediting schedule, completion of field paperwork, expediting materials.</li>\n  <li>Support Operations and Project Manager with client communication regarding project schedules.</li>\n  <li>Collaborate with project supervisor to prepare and submit Change Orders to the customer.</li>\n  <li>Assist and support Project Manager by attending project meetings with General Contractor, Owner, Architect, and others.</li>\n  <li>Establish good working relationship with other team members.</li>\n  <li>Foster positive communications and relationships with team members, management, vendors and clients</li>\n  <li>Keep up to date on industry trends and developments.</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Key Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Candidate must possess at least Bachelor's Degree/Post Graduate Diploma/Professional Degree in Engineering (Civil) or Engineering (Metal Fabrication/Tool &amp; Dry/Welding) or equivalent. <strong>(Degree is recognized by BCA will be an advantage)</strong></li>\n  <li>At least 2 Year(s) of working experience in the same field <strong>(Metal Work) </strong>is required.</li>\n  <li>Preferably Senior Executive specialized in Engineering - Civil/Construction/Structural or equivalent.</li>\n  <li>Excellent organizational skills</li>\n  <li>Ability to think big picture and take into account long-term implications of ones’ actions</li>\n  <li>Passion for looking for ways to improve individual and/or company performance</li>\n  <li>Commitment to exceeding customers’ expectations</li>\n  <li>Intermediate level in Procore, CMiC, or similar construction software</li>\n  <li>Intermediate to advanced level in Microsoft Office Applications (Word, Excel and Outlook)</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 4,
